The paper discusses the use of deep recurrent neural networks for time series prediction, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), systems and control (cs.SY), and computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV). Given that the paper focuses on the use of neural networks for time series prediction, cs.LG and cs.NE are the most likely sub-categories. However, since the paper also discusses the use of dynamic programming and matrix operations for training the neural network, cs.SY and cs.AI are also likely sub-categories. Finally, since the paper uses the example of epileptic seizure suppression, which involves analyzing medical data, cs.CV is also a possible sub-category.
